President Obama announced his intent to nominate Jacqueline A. Berrien as Chair of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. Berrien has a background in fighting for underrepresented communities and protecting basic rights. She has served as Associate Director-Counsel of the NAACP Legal Defense and Educational Fund and has experience in promoting political participation and removing barriers to civic engagement. Berrien has also taught in trial advocacy programs at Fordham and Harvard law schools. She is a graduate of Harvard Law School and received her Bachelor of Arts degree from Oberlin College.